<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
When you use another person&#8217;s ideas or words in your writing, include their name and any relevant 
page number(s), in parentheses, immediately following the cited material. (Note: where the article 
is only one page long, page numbers are not needed).
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (Smith).
</blockquote>
<br>
Or include the title of the work in your sentence, with the relevant page number(s) in parentheses 
(if necessary).
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith suggests that &#34;the default position is markedly affected&#34;.
</blockquote>
